The structure was empty at the time, and police say only a few people received minor injuries.
MARCEL BROWN, BARBER AND BYSTANDER, SAYING:
"I was walking down the street right here and I got maybe right here and I just heard a big kaboom and I was like wow I see a lot of smoke and I was looking and I heard a lot of noise and you couldn't really see and I started walking away and then you saw the debris coming into the street right there and I was praying to God that nobody was in the building right there but basically that's what happened. It was an old building, they're doing construction over here."
JULIE SON, NEARBY RESIDENT, SAYING:
"I was in my building, I was drifting off to sleep and I felt this shake and this really loud noise and heard people screaming."
The four-story building was home to a beauty supply store until last year.
